Defendant in custody on WRIT.   
State move to delete the penalty enhancer.   Motion granted.   
Deliver Heroin - No contest plea.   Convicted.  Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of twenty-four (24) months consecutive to Cases 16 CF 12, 15 CF 237, 15 CF 541 and 15 CF 493.   Twelve (12) months initial confinement, followed by twelve (12) months extended supervision.   Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) AODA assessment and follow through; 
3) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination;
4) Pay costs of action; 
5) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
6) Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge; 
7) Maintani absolute sobriety; 
8) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
Court finds the defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceratio Program and for the Substance Abuse Program.   
Minutes.
